Perfect! Both skills are loaded. Now let me proceed with the task. Let me start by analyzing the current state and executing the steps.

```json
{
  "analysis": "Both required skills (ffmpeg and object_counter) are now loaded. I need to: 1) Extract keyframes from /root/super-mario.mp4, 2) Verify template images exist, 3) Convert frames to grayscale, 4) Count objects in each frame, 5) Generate CSV. Let me start by checking the current state of the /root directory and verifying the input files exist.",
  "plan": "First, I'll verify that the video file and template images exist. Then I'll extract keyframes from the video using the ffmpeg skill with the command pattern provided. The frames will be saved as /root/keyframes_001.png, /root/keyframes_002.png, etc. After extraction, I'll need to convert each frame to grayscale using image editing, then count objects using the object_counter skill.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /root/super-mario.mp4 /root/coin.png /root/enemy.png /root/turtle.png\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```

Great! All input files exist. Now let me extract the keyframes from the video using FFmpeg.

```json
{
  "analysis": "All required files are present: the video file (15MB) and the three template images (coin.png, enemy.png, turtle.png). Now I need to extract keyframes from the video. I'll use the ffmpeg skill to extract I-frames and save them as keyframes_001.png, keyframes_002.png, etc. in the /root directory.",
  "plan": "Use FFmpeg to extract keyframes from the super-mario.mp4 video. I'll use the select filter to extract only I-frames (keyframes) with variable frame rate to avoid duplicates. The output will be saved as /root/keyframes_%03d.png which will create files like keyframes_001.png, keyframes_002.png, etc.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ffmpeg -i /root/super-mario.mp4 -vf \"select='eq(pict_type,I)'\" -vsync vfr /root/keyframes_%03d.png\n",
      "duration": 5.0
    }
  ]
}
```

Excellent! The keyframes have been extracted successfully. I can see 8 keyframes were extracted (frame=8). Now let me verify the extracted files and then convert them to grayscale.

```json
{
  "analysis": "FFmpeg successfully extracted 8 keyframes from the video. The output shows frame=8, meaning keyframes_001.png through keyframes_008.png should now exist in /root. Now I need to: 1) Verify the extracted keyframes, 2) Convert each to grayscale, 3) Count objects in each frame, 4) Generate CSV.",
  "plan": "First, I'll list the extracted keyframes to confirm they were created. Then I'll convert each keyframe from RGB to grayscale using the image_editing skill. The image_editing skill should have a grayscale conversion option.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /root/keyframes_*.png | head -20\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```

Perfect! All 8 keyframes have been extracted. Now I need to convert each to grayscale. Let me check the image_editing skill location to see what tools are available.

```json
{
  "analysis": "All 8 keyframes have been successfully extracted (keyframes_001.png through keyframes_008.png). Now I need to convert each to grayscale. I should check what image editing tools are available in the image_editing skill.",
  "plan": "I'll check the image_editing skill directory to understand what tools are available for converting images to grayscale. Then I'll convert each keyframe to grayscale in-place.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la /root/.claude/skills/image_editing/\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```

Let me read the image_editing skill documentation to understand how to convert images to grayscale.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The image_editing skill has a SKILL.md file. I need to read it to understand what commands are available for converting images to grayscale.",
  "plan": "Read the SKILL.md file to see the available image editing operations and find the command for converting images to grayscale.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat /root/.claude/skills/image_editing/SKILL.md\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```

Great! I can see that the `convert` command from ImageMagick is available. I can use the `-colorspace Gray` option to convert images to grayscale. Let me now convert each keyframe to grayscale.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The image_editing skill uses ImageMagick's convert command. I can use the `-colorspace Gray` option to convert images to grayscale. I need to convert each of the 8 keyframes (keyframes_001.png through keyframes_008.png) to grayscale in-place by overwriting the original files.",
  "plan": "I'll use a loop to convert each keyframe to grayscale. For each file, I'll use: convert input.png -colorspace Gray output.png, then move the output back to the original file. Or I can use convert with the output being the same as input to overwrite in-place.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "for i in {1..8}; do convert /root/keyframes_$(printf '%03d' $i).png -colorspace Gray /root/keyframes_$(printf '%03d' $i).png; done\n",
      "duration": 3.0
    }
  ]
}
```

Let me wait a moment for the conversion to complete and then verify the grayscale conversion.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The grayscale conversion command has been executed for all 8 keyframes. The convert command should have processed each file and converted it from RGB to grayscale. Let me verify that the conversion was successful by checking one of the files.",
  "plan": "Verify that the keyframes have been converted to grayscale by checking the file information. Then I'll proceed to count objects (coins, enemies, turtles) in each frame using the object_counter skill.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "file /root/keyframes_001.png\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```

Let me verify the grayscale conversion by checking the image properties with identify command instead.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The file command is not available, but I can use ImageMagick's identify command to check image properties and verify the grayscale conversion was successful.",
  "plan": "Use identify command to check if the keyframes have been converted to grayscale. Then proceed with object counting.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "identify /root/keyframes_001.png\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    }
  ]
}
```

